reviews.review: Somehow manages to be insulting to fans who enjoyed the Last Jedi subversion of Star Wars tropes as well as those fans who held the old school Star Wars legacy dear. Kind of a marvel in that sense. It's utterly nonsensical and mystifyingly contrived.

Forget all the critics and naysayers. This is an imperfect and a great conclusion to the saga. They did a great job blending the old with the new and I love the cameos. A lot going on here for sure but I think the story lines and finale are great. We will miss our beloved Princess, Han Luke, CPO, R2D2, Lando and Chewy! Thank you so much George Lucas through JJ Abrams for all of it. Well done!
it was blatant pandering, the worst thing i have seen since solo: a cash grab story

Overall a disappointing end to a almost great (Last Jedi) saga.
It felt like mash up of different takes glued together to make a fan film, with the story jumping so fast if you blinked you would literally miss it. Plot points were to rushed, no character development with scenes that literally left us laughing but were not meant to.
With a ending scene that literally had us rolling our eyes chuckling saying to each other "they can't be serious" 
We feel we have wasted our time and money and would have prefered to see the Holiday Special
It was so intense! It was everything I was hoping for in terms of the story and outcome. It was an emotional roller-coaster, but overall, it was worth it.
Meh, way to voluted. Doesn't feel like the ending the Skywalker saga deserves. Way too many unanswered questions, plot holes, and plot threads left open.
Not perfect but very satisfying conclusion to the Skywalker Saga. Loved it!

Disappointing. It felt rushed and cramped that I really had a hard time to enjoy and appreciate the story. Especially since I love all the 8 movies before this. I don't know what the heck went inside JJ Abram's mind when he orchestrated this... mess... The Romance was wonderful though. If there was anything good that came out of this train wreck, it was definitely the romance.

A remix of RETURN OF THE JEDI. More special effects and a jumble of fast edits and unexplained characters can't cover for weak storytelling.  The bright spot is Adam Driver whose talent pushes through the film's weaknesses.

By the way, Episode 8 isn't necessary for understanding this one.
